font-size:11pt">.</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">  Perhaps most importantly, cycling offers the most obvious, dramatic and immediate solution to the problem of congestion in urban areas.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">EXECUTIVE SUMMARY </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">In my opinion:</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 46.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Cycling is not safe</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> at the moment</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 46.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">The single biggest contributor to poor cyclist </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">safety is driver behaviour and attitudes</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 46.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Local and central Government must actively challenge public opinion on many aspects of driving, with the aim of making poor driving as socially unacceptable as drink driving</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 46.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">The Government should conduct a trial of </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">providing subsidised cycle helmets fitted with cameras to cyclists, and the means to upload the footage to police stations </span></li></ul><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 31.35pt; padding-left:4.65pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">As a cyclist</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">  I have been subject to the following b</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">ehaviour from drivers</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">:</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 46.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Cars overtaking me at </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">high speed </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">(40mph) </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">leaving a gap </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">between us </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">of less than 12 inches</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> (daily)</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">.</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">  I have had to swerve or move my body to avoid making contact on several occasions.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 46.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Being tailgated (less than 2 feet from my back wheel) in a deliberate attempt to intimidate me and force me to the side of the ro</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">ad to allow a car to pass</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> (where there is insufficient room to do so safely)</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 46.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Having to take evasive action (swerve, very hard braking) to avoid a car pulling out in front of me/cutting across my path in a </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">deliberate</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> attempt to assert</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> their right of way when the right of way is mine.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 46.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Being driven at in a deliberate aggressive act to intimidat</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">e</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">.  On one occasion the car made contact with me.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 46.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Overtaking me on the right whilst I am signalling right and in the middle of the road. </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 46.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">V</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">erbal </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">abuse.</span></li></ul><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-indent:36pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Please note I am referring above to </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">deliberate</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> acts, not mistakes/failure to look/see.</span></p><ol start="2" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 31.35pt; padding-left:4.65pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">In the press</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> the following attitudes and opinions are regularly expressed and accepted as fact:</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 46.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Roads are for cars, not other road users</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 46.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Car drivers have more r</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">ights because they pay road tax</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 46.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Enforcing driving laws is a form of taxation</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 46.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Law breaking car drivers are victims </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 46.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Car drivers are free to choose which laws to abide by and which to ignore.</span></li></ul><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 54pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="3" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 31.35pt; padding-left:4.65pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">I believe there is a direct link between the attitudes expressed </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">in the press/ in public and the behaviour I see on the roads every day.  There is an urgent need to tackle the attitudes head-on and highlight the real damage that the behaviours do.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="4" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 31.35pt; padding-left:4.65pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">The government has a role to shape public attitudes in certain arenas.  </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">It has been very successful in changing public attitudes to drink driving, for example, and turned this into a socially unacceptable practice.  The government needs to do the same for all aspects of bad and aggressive/selfish driving.</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="5" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 31.35pt; padding-left:4.65pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">The Government needs</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> to undertake a public awareness campaign that takes on the a</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">ssumptions listed in paragraph 2, and demonstrate</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> the consequences of bad driving in a robust manner, with the aim of making it socially unacceptable.  </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">T</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">he following messages </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">are in urgent need o</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">f promotion</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">:</span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 64.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Paying road tax does not give you more rights th</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">an other road users.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 64.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Driving laws are enforced because the consequence of bad driving is someone’s death.</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">  </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 64.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Bad driving results in the deaths of </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">thousands</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> of people every year.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 64.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">The Government is</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> not going to apologise for enforcing the law.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 64.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">People who break the law are perpetrators; the third parties who suffer the consequences are victims.  </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Car drivers </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">who are fined </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">are </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">therefore </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">not victims</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 64.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">People</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> should not</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> behave in cars in ways that are com</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">pletely unacceptable in </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">any</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> other area of life –</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> would a young </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">man force an old lady out of the </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">way on the pavement</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">? </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Do taller people deliberately intimidate smaller people? </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> Do pedestrians put other pedestrians in danger just to get passed them quickly?</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> In a car we see it every day</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> and it should be</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> no more acceptable there</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">.</span></li></ul></ul><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">It is particularly important for the Government to link criminality and bad driving.  This could be achieved by some pointed comparisons.  Imagine two burglars lamenting their bad lu</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">ck at being caught, interspersed with footage of the victims trying to deal with the trauma.  Then replay the same scene but with two drivers complaining about being fined for speeding interspersed with footage of parents visiting their son, a road acciden</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">t victim, in hospital.  The first conversation is morally offensive, the second not only acceptable but repeated up and down the country every day.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 72pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="6" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 31.35pt; padding-left:4.65pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Many cyclists have equipped themselves with cycle cameras to film instances of bad driver behaviour. </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">The G</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">overnment c</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">ould trial the provision of free or subsidised cycle helmets fitted with cycle cams to any cyclist who wants one, and instructions on how to upload any footage to police (say, by email).  </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">Police forces should set</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">up special units to view and ac</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">t on footage sent to them.   Additionally</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">, cyclists should be obliged to hand over footage on demand at random, for it to be inspected for any evidence of cyclists themselves breaking the Highway Code.   </span></li></ol><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">If a significant proportion of cyclists are record</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">ing their rides, not only will this assist prosecution of aggressive drivers but it will have a deterrent effect.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">To enhance the deterrent effect, the Government could promote the provision of dummy cycle cams (available for sale at a low price) for any c</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">yclist who does not want the weight of a real camera on their helmet</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt"> but wants to deter aggressiveness</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">January 2014</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri;